When I&#39;m writing unit-tests, I generally try to pre-empt mistakes I (or perhaps another developer) is likely to come along and make.

Take this class `Foo` for example, which has an equality-operator:

    struct Foo {
      int m_foo;

      bool operator==(const Foo&amp; other) const {
        return m_foo == other.m_foo;
      }
    };

    // test code
    TEST(FooEquality, Equal) {
      Foo f1, f2;
      f1.m_foo = 1;
      f2.m_foo = 1;

      EXPECT_EQ(f1, f2);
    }

    TEST(FooEquality, NotEqual) {
      Foo f1, f2;
